    <!-- Tips - Lose Weight -->
    <string name="tip_lose_1">Eat at a 500 kcal deficit daily. This creates roughly 0.5 kg of fat loss per week without harming your metabolism.</string>
    <string name="tip_lose_2">Prioritize protein in every meal. Protein keeps you full longer and prevents muscle loss while in a calorie deficit.</string>
    <string name="tip_lose_3">Avoid liquid calories — sugary drinks, juice, and alcohol add up fast without making you feel full.</string>
    <string name="tip_lose_4">Meal timing: Eat your largest meal before 2pm. Evening meals should be lighter — mostly protein and vegetables.</string>
    <string name="tip_lose_5">Hydration: Drink a full glass of water before each meal. It reduces hunger and helps you eat less naturally.</string>

    <!-- Tips - Gain Muscle -->
    <string name="tip_gain_1">Eat at a 300 kcal surplus daily. More than this leads to unnecessary fat gain. Slow and steady builds lean muscle.</string>
    <string name="tip_gain_2">Aim for 1.6–2.2g of protein per kg of bodyweight. For a 65kg person that is 104–143g of protein per day.</string>
    <string name="tip_gain_3">Carbohydrates are your friend. They fuel your workouts and replenish glycogen. Do not cut them when bulking.</string>
    <string name="tip_gain_4">Meal timing: Have a protein and carb meal within 1 hour after training. This is your most important meal of the day.</string>
    <string name="tip_gain_5">Hydration: Aim for 3 litres of water daily. Muscles are 75% water — dehydration directly reduces strength.</string>

    <!-- Tips - Maintain -->
    <string name="tip_maintain_1">Eat at your TDEE — not above, not below. Use the app daily to stay consistent and aware of your intake.</string>
    <string name="tip_maintain_2">Balance your plate: half vegetables, a quarter protein, a quarter carbohydrates. This ratio works for most people.</string>
    <string name="tip_maintain_3">Do not skip meals. Skipping leads to overeating later. Three balanced meals and one small snack is ideal.</string>
    <string name="tip_maintain_4">Meal timing: Breakfast within 1 hour of waking keeps your metabolism active throughout the day.</string>
    <string name="tip_maintain_5">Hydration: Drink at least 2 litres of water daily. Thirst is often mistaken for hunger — drink first, then decide.</string>
